<subSubSection lastPageId="19" lastPageNumber="20" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="16.[151,1437,629,1110]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,344,906,931]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Description.</emphasis>
Small-sized pontoniine shrimp with depressed body. Carapace smooth; antennal tooth sharp. Rostrum long, compressed, more or less straight, with slightly ascendant tip overreaching distal margin of scaphocerite blade; dorsal lamina with four large dorsal teeth all situated anterior to orbit; most-distal portion of rostrum toothless; ventral lamina with one tooth situated slightly anterior to half-length of rostrum; proximolateral rostral lamina well developed, with blunt supraocular lobe adjacent to rostral base. Pterygostomial angle bluntly produced anteriorly.
</paragraph>
